A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Environment – Tire Recycling Fee – Alterations
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Department of the Environment, instead of the Board of
4 Public Works, to establish a tire recycling fee to be imposed on the first sale of a new
5 tire in the State by a tire dealer; requiring the Department to set the tire recycling
6 fee at a certain amount beginning on a certain date; authorizing the Department to
7 adjust the tire recycling fee for inflation at certain time intervals; prohibiting the tire
8 recycling fee from exceeding a certain amount; and generally relating to the tire
9 recycling fee.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
11 Article – Environment
12 Section 9–228(g) and 9–274
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2014 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
