12 (3) For a sale made by a tire dealer to a person who resells tires, the tire
13 dealer shall separately state its recycling fees paid by the tire dealer on the invoice or other
14 document of sale.
15 (4) (i) Each tire dealer shall:
16 1. Pay the tire recycling fee; and
17 2. Complete and submit, under oath, a return and remit the
18 fees to the Comptroller of the Treasury on or before the 21st day of the month that follows
19 the month in which the sale was made, and for other periods and on other dates that the
20 Comptroller specifies by regulation, including periods for which no fees were due.
21 (ii) For periods beginning after December 31, 2026, a person shall
22 file a tire recycling fee return electronically.
23 (5) A tire dealer who timely files a tire recycling fee return and pays the
24 tire recycling fees due is allowed, for the expense of administering and paying the fee, a
25 credit equal to 0.6% of the gross amount of tire recycling fees that the tire dealer is to pay
26 to the Comptroller.
27 (6) If the amount of the tire recycling fee is separately stated in a retail
28 sale, the tire recycling fee is not subject to any tax under Title 11 of the Tax – General
29 Article or Title 13 of the Transportation Article.
30 (7) At the end of each quarter, the Comptroller shall forward all tire
31 recycling fees to the Used Tire Cleanup and Recycling Fund, less the costs of
32 administration.

